<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-22T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-22T16:00:00-05:00" n="614" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500. A 4e/23: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-22T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 22,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your April 11, 10 a.m.</p>
                        <p>For Arnold.</p>
                        <p>W. A. Burns is hereby appointed Associate Member of Tariff Revision
                            Commission. Offer of voluntary services appreciated but under statute
                            can not be accepted. Confer with Burns and telegraph amount regarded as
                            reasonable compensation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>